Product Id: National Population Health Survey: Household Component, Cross-sectional
Source: Statistics Canada, National Population Health Survey, 1994/95 cross sectional sample, health file
Level of chronic stress reported by the population aged 18 and over, based on their responses to a series of 17 questions about their personal situation.
Bootstrapping techniques were used to produce the coefficient of variation (CV) and 95% confidence intervals (CIs).
Data with a coefficient of variation (CV) from 16.6% to 33.3% are identified by an (E) and should be interpreted with caution.
Data with a coefficient of variation (CV) greater than 33.3% were suppressed (F) due to extreme sampling variability.
Comparable data are not available for 1996/97 and 1998/99.

The cross-sectional component of the National Population Health Survey (NPHS) has been taken over by the Canadian Community Health Survey (CCHS). The table (104-0037) was archived.  Due to a change in definition, data in CCHS 2000/01 table (105-0038) are not comparable.
